# ⚡ 3. REST Operations (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

You already saw `@PostMapping`. Now here’s the full set.

---

## 🔹 CREATE → POST

```java
@PostMapping
public Student createStudent(@RequestBody Student student) {
    return studentService.save(student);
}
```

---

## 🔹 READ → GET

### Get all

```java
@GetMapping
public List<Student> getAll() {
    return studentService.getAll();
}
```

### Get by ID

```java
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public Student getById(@PathVariable Long id) {
    return studentService.getById(id);
}
```

---

## 🔹 UPDATE → PUT

```java
@PutMapping("/{id}")
public Student update(@PathVariable Long id, @RequestBody Student student) {
    return studentService.update(id, student);
}
```

---

## 🔹 DELETE → DELETE

```java
@DeleteMapping("/{id}")
public String delete(@PathVariable Long id) {
    studentService.delete(id);
    return "Deleted";
}
```

---

# 🔧 4. What classes you need to change for REST?

Here’s where most beginners mess up.

### ❌ Wrong thinking:

“Only controller needs change”

### ✅ Reality:

| Operation | Controller | Service | Repository | Entity |
| --------- | ---------- | ------- | ---------- | ------ |
| POST      | ✔          | ✔       | ✔          | ✔      |
| GET       | ✔          | ✔       | ✔          | ❌      |
| PUT       | ✔          | ✔       | ✔          | ❌      |
| DELETE    | ✔          | ✔       | ✔          | ❌      |

👉 Repository often doesn’t need changes because `JpaRepository` already gives:

* `save()`
* `findById()`
* `findAll()`
* `deleteById()`

